{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":605,"text":"I essentially drag sledges for a living,"},{"time":2359,"text":"so it doesn't take an awful lot to flummox me intellectually,"},{"time":5543,"text":"but I'm going to read this question"},{"time":7085,"text":"from an interview earlier this year:"},{"time":9552,"text":"\"Philosophically, does the constant supply of information"},{"time":12944,"text":"steal our ability to imagine"},{"time":15679,"text":"or replace our dreams of achieving?"},{"time":18495,"text":"After all, if it is being done somewhere by someone,"},{"time":21281,"text":"and we can participate virtually,"},{"time":23584,"text":"then why bother leaving the house?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":27085,"text":"I'm usually introduced as a polar explorer."},{"time":29734,"text":"I'm not sure that's the most progressive or 21st-century"},{"time":32035,"text":"of job titles, but I've spent more than two percent now"},{"time":36801,"text":"of my entire life living in a tent inside the Arctic Circle,"},{"time":40529,"text":"so I get out of the house a fair bit."},{"time":44056,"text":"And in my nature, I guess, I am a doer of things"},{"time":47603,"text":"more than I am a spectator or a contemplator of things,"},{"time":52095,"text":"and it's that dichotomy, the gulf between ideas and action"},{"time":56319,"text":"that I'm going to try and explore briefly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59185,"text":"The pithiest answer to the question \"why?\""},{"time":62518,"text":"that's been dogging me for the last 12 years"},{"time":64886,"text":"was credited certainly to this chap, the rakish-looking gentleman"},{"time":67670,"text":"standing at the back, second from the left,"},{"time":69926,"text":"George Lee Mallory. Many of you will know his name."},{"time":72564,"text":"In 1924 he was last seen disappearing into the clouds"},{"time":76553,"text":"near the summit of Mt. Everest."},{"time":78227,"text":"He may or may not have been the first person to climb Everest,"},{"time":81482,"text":"more than 30 years before Edmund Hillary."},{"time":83458,"text":"No one knows if he got to the top. It's still a mystery."},{"time":86154,"text":"But he was credited with coining the phrase, \"Because it's there.\""},{"time":89223,"text":"Now I'm not actually sure that he did say that."},{"time":91913,"text":"There's very little evidence to suggest it, but what he did say"},{"time":94239,"text":"is actually far nicer,"},{"time":96719,"text":"and again, I've printed this. I'm going to read it out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99773,"text":"\"The first question which you will ask"},{"time":101727,"text":"and which I must try to answer is this:"},{"time":104224,"text":"What is the use of climbing Mt. Everest?"},{"time":108000,"text":"And my answer must at once be, it is no use."},{"time":110688,"text":"There is not the slightest prospect of any gain whatsoever."},{"time":114449,"text":"Oh, we may learn a little about the behavior"},{"time":116322,"text":"of the human body at high altitudes,"},{"time":118404,"text":"and possibly medical men may turn our observation"},{"time":121068,"text":"to some account for the purposes of aviation,"},{"time":124097,"text":"but otherwise nothing will come of it."},{"time":126297,"text":"We shall not bring back a single bit of gold or silver,"},{"time":128683,"text":"and not a gem, nor any coal or iron."},{"time":131282,"text":"We shall not find a single foot of earth that can be planted"},{"time":134081,"text":"with crops to raise food. So it is no use."},{"time":138223,"text":"If you cannot understand that there is something in man"},{"time":139882,"text":"which responds to the challenge of this mountain"},{"time":142554,"text":"and goes out to meet it, that the struggle"},{"time":145777,"text":"is the struggle of life itself upward and forever upward,"},{"time":150231,"text":"then you won't see why we go."},{"time":153479,"text":"What we get from this adventure is just sheer joy,"},{"time":156608,"text":"and joy, after all, is the end of life."},{"time":159542,"text":"We don't live to eat and make money."},{"time":161745,"text":"We eat and make money to be able to enjoy life."},{"time":164207,"text":"That is what life means, and that is what life is for.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":169115,"text":"Mallory's argument that leaving the house,"},{"time":172569,"text":"embarking on these grand adventures is joyful and fun,"},{"time":175012,"text":"however, doesn't tally that neatly with my own experience."},{"time":178918,"text":"The furthest I've ever got away from my front door"},{"time":182320,"text":"was in the spring of 2004. I still don't know exactly"},{"time":185464,"text":"what came over me, but my plan was to make"},{"time":187971,"text":"a solo and unsupported crossing of the Arctic Ocean."},{"time":192214,"text":"I planned essentially to walk from the north coast of Russia"},{"time":194771,"text":"to the North Pole, and then to carry on to the north coast of Canada."},{"time":198103,"text":"No one had ever done this. I was 26 at the time."},{"time":201011,"text":"A lot of experts were saying it was impossible,"},{"time":203263,"text":"and my mum certainly wasn't very keen on the idea."},{"time":206617,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":208970,"text":"The journey from a small weather station on the north coast"},{"time":211896,"text":"of Siberia up to my final starting point,"},{"time":214081,"text":"the edge of the pack ice, the coast of the Arctic Ocean,"},{"time":216633,"text":"took about five hours, and if anyone watched fearless"},{"time":220094,"text":"Felix Baumgartner going up, rather than just coming down,"},{"time":223406,"text":"you'll appreciate the sense of apprehension,"},{"time":226010,"text":"as I sat in a helicopter thundering north,"},{"time":229322,"text":"and the sense, I think if anything, of impending doom."},{"time":231979,"text":"I sat there wondering what on Earth I had gotten myself into."},{"time":235669,"text":"There was a bit of fun, a bit of joy."},{"time":237713,"text":"I was 26. I remember sitting there"},{"time":239554,"text":"looking down at my sledge. I had my skis ready to go,"},{"time":242146,"text":"I had a satellite phone, a pump-action shotgun"},{"time":244387,"text":"in case I was attacked by a polar bear."},{"time":246410,"text":"I remember looking out of the window and seeing the second helicopter."},{"time":248701,"text":"We were both thundering through this incredible Siberian dawn,"},{"time":252187,"text":"and part of me felt a bit like a cross between Jason Bourne"},{"time":255052,"text":"and Wilfred Thesiger. Part of me"},{"time":257944,"text":"felt quite proud of myself, but mostly I was just utterly terrified."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264266,"text":"And that journey lasted 10 weeks, 72 days."},{"time":266356,"text":"I didn't see anyone else. We took this photo next to the helicopter."},{"time":268855,"text":"Beyond that, I didn't see anyone for 10 weeks."},{"time":271414,"text":"The North Pole is slap bang in the middle of the sea,"},{"time":273356,"text":"so I'm traveling over the frozen surface of the Arctic Ocean."},{"time":276617,"text":"NASA described conditions that year as the worst since records began."},{"time":280727,"text":"I was dragging 180 kilos of food and fuel and supplies,"},{"time":284383,"text":"about 400 pounds. The average temperature for the 10 weeks"},{"time":286984,"text":"was minus 35. Minus 50 was the coldest."},{"time":289675,"text":"So again, there wasn't an awful lot of joy or fun to be had."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296954,"text":"One of the magical things about this journey, however,"},{"time":298487,"text":"is that because I'm walking over the sea,"},{"time":300590,"text":"over this floating, drifting, shifting crust of ice"},{"time":304652,"text":"that's floating on top of the Arctic Ocean is"},{"time":306847,"text":"it's an environment that's in a constant state of flux."},{"time":308795,"text":"The ice is always moving, breaking up, drifting around,"},{"time":311141,"text":"refreezing, so the scenery that I saw for nearly 3 months"},{"time":314601,"text":"was unique to me. No one else will ever, could ever,"},{"time":318048,"text":"possibly see the views, the vistas, that I saw for 10 weeks."},{"time":323077,"text":"And that, I guess, is probably the finest argument for leaving the house."},{"time":327040,"text":"I can try to tell you what it was like,"},{"time":330922,"text":"but you'll never know what it was like,"},{"time":332767,"text":"and the more I try to explain that I felt lonely,"},{"time":335695,"text":"I was the only human being in 5.4 million square-miles,"},{"time":339414,"text":"it was cold, nearly minus 75 with windchill on a bad day,"},{"time":343719,"text":"the more words fall short, and I'm unable to do it justice."},{"time":347551,"text":"And it seems to me, therefore, that the doing,"},{"time":351742,"text":"you know, to try to experience, to engage, to endeavor,"},{"time":357040,"text":"rather than to watch and to wonder, that's where"},{"time":362426,"text":"the real meat of life is to be found,"},{"time":364652,"text":"the juice that we can suck out of our hours and days."},{"time":368596,"text":"And I would add a cautionary note here, however."},{"time":371079,"text":"In my experience, there is something addictive"},{"time":373167,"text":"about tasting life at the very edge of what's humanly possible."},{"time":377606,"text":"Now I don't just mean in the field of"},{"time":379841,"text":"daft macho Edwardian style derring-do,"},{"time":382128,"text":"but also in the fields of pancreatic cancer,"},{"time":384321,"text":"there is something addictive about this, and in my case,"},{"time":386228,"text":"I think polar expeditions are perhaps not that far removed"},{"time":388778,"text":"from having a crack habit."},{"time":390160,"text":"I can't explain quite how good it is until you've tried it,"},{"time":393865,"text":"but it has the capacity to burn up all the money I can get my hands on,"},{"time":397682,"text":"to ruin every relationship I've ever had,"},{"time":401260,"text":"so be careful what you wish for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":405661,"text":"Mallory postulated that there is something in man"},{"time":408042,"text":"that responds to the challenge of the mountain,"},{"time":410682,"text":"and I wonder if that's the case whether there's something"},{"time":412708,"text":"in the challenge itself, in the endeavor, and particularly"},{"time":415765,"text":"in the big, unfinished, chunky challenges that face humanity"},{"time":418877,"text":"that call out to us, and in my experience that's certainly the case."},{"time":423193,"text":"There is one unfinished challenge"},{"time":424973,"text":"that's been calling out to me for most of my adult life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428245,"text":"Many of you will know the story."},{"time":429673,"text":"This is a photo of Captain Scott and his team."},{"time":432264,"text":"Scott set out just over a hundred years ago to try"},{"time":434137,"text":"to become the first person to reach the South Pole."},{"time":437404,"text":"No one knew what was there. It was utterly unmapped"},{"time":439228,"text":"at the time. We knew more about the surface of the moon"},{"time":441253,"text":"than we did about the heart of Antarctica."},{"time":444000,"text":"Scott, as many of you will know, was beaten to it"},{"time":446916,"text":"by Roald Amundsen and his Norwegian team,"},{"time":449209,"text":"who used dogs and dogsleds. Scott's team were on foot,"},{"time":451564,"text":"all five of them wearing harnesses and dragging around sledges,"},{"time":453985,"text":"and they arrived at the pole to find the Norwegian flag already there,"},{"time":458417,"text":"I'd imagine pretty bitter and demoralized."},{"time":461675,"text":"All five of them turned and started walking back to the coast"},{"time":463945,"text":"and all five died on that return journey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467533,"text":"There is a sort of misconception nowadays that"},{"time":469767,"text":"it's all been done in the fields of exploration and adventure."},{"time":473393,"text":"When I talk about Antarctica, people often say,"},{"time":474680,"text":"\"Hasn't, you know, that's interesting,"},{"time":475970,"text":"hasn't that Blue Peter presenter just done it on a bike?\""},{"time":479163,"text":"Or, \"That's nice. You know, my grandmother's going"},{"time":482753,"text":"on a cruise to Antarctica next year. You know."},{"time":485383,"text":"Is there a chance you'll see her there?\""},{"time":488249,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":490067,"text":"But Scott's journey remains unfinished."},{"time":493281,"text":"No one has ever walked from the very coast of Antarctica"},{"time":495608,"text":"to the South Pole and back again."},{"time":497405,"text":"It is, arguably, the most audacious endeavor"},{"time":500179,"text":"of that Edwardian golden age of exploration,"},{"time":502804,"text":"and it seemed to me high time, given everything"},{"time":505357,"text":"we have figured out in the century since"},{"time":507278,"text":"from scurvy to solar panels, that it was high time"},{"time":510859,"text":"someone had a go at finishing the job."},{"time":512636,"text":"So that's precisely what I'm setting out to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":515332,"text":"This time next year, in October, I'm leading a team of three."},{"time":517900,"text":"It will take us about four months to make this return journey."},{"time":520759,"text":"That's the scale. The red line is obviously halfway to the pole."},{"time":523812,"text":"We have to turn around and come back again."},{"time":525206,"text":"I'm well aware of the irony of telling you that we will be"},{"time":527453,"text":"blogging and tweeting. You'll be able to live"},{"time":530188,"text":"vicariously and virtually through this journey"},{"time":532621,"text":"in a way that no one has ever before."},{"time":535628,"text":"And it'll also be a four-month chance for me to finally"},{"time":538211,"text":"come up with a pithy answer to the question, \"Why?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":542085,"text":"And our lives today are safer and more comfortable"},{"time":547018,"text":"than they have ever been. There certainly isn't much call"},{"time":549600,"text":"for explorers nowadays. My career advisor at school"},{"time":553458,"text":"never mentioned it as an option."},{"time":556099,"text":"If I wanted to know, for example,"},{"time":558521,"text":"how many stars were in the Milky Way,"},{"time":560817,"text":"how old those giant heads on Easter Island were,"},{"time":563396,"text":"most of you could find that out right now"},{"time":565521,"text":"without even standing up."},{"time":568347,"text":"And yet, if I've learned anything in nearly 12 years now"},{"time":571112,"text":"of dragging heavy things around cold places,"},{"time":574199,"text":"it is that true, real inspiration and growth"},{"time":578158,"text":"only comes from adversity and from challenge,"},{"time":582418,"text":"from stepping away from what's comfortable and familiar"},{"time":585434,"text":"and stepping out into the unknown."},{"time":587915,"text":"In life, we all have tempests to ride and poles to walk to,"},{"time":591456,"text":"and I think metaphorically speaking, at least,"},{"time":593265,"text":"we could all benefit from getting outside the house"},{"time":596135,"text":"a little more often, if only we could summon up the courage."},{"time":600016,"text":"I certainly would implore you to open the door just a little bit"},{"time":603241,"text":"and take a look at what's outside."},{"time":606137,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":607365,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}